    name: "Le Grand Ritz",
    description: `Nestled at the iconic Place Vendôme in the heart of Paris, Le Grand Ritz is the undisputed jewel of French hospitality. Since its founding in 1898 by César Ritz, the hotel has set the global benchmark for luxury, elegance, and impeccable service. Every corridor whispers history — from Coco Chanel, who called the hotel her home for more than three decades, to Ernest Hemingway, who reportedly liberated the Ritz bar at the end of World War II.

The hotel's 142 rooms and suites are masterpieces of French craftsmanship, adorned with hand-stitched silk draperies, gilded Louis XVI furniture, and original artworks curated from across France. Each bathroom is clad in Carrara marble with deep soaking tubs and bespoke Ritz Paris toiletries crafted exclusively by master perfumers. Floor-to-ceiling windows frame views of the intimate Vendôme garden or the glittering Parisian cityscape.

Dining at Le Grand Ritz is a pilgrimage for gastronomes worldwide. The two-Michelin-starred L'Espadon serves classical French haute cuisine reimagined with contemporary precision, while the legendary Bar Hemingway — presided over by celebrated head bartsman Colin Field — pours some of the world's most extraordinary cocktails. The hotel's pastry team produces handcrafted chocolates, macarons, and seasonal confections that are shipped globally.

The Ritz Club Paris wellness sanctuary spans 1,500 square metres underground, featuring an indoor swimming pool inspired by a Roman bath, a hammam, a flotation pool, and fourteen treatment rooms offering exclusive La Prairie and Ritz Paris signature therapies. Personal trainers, nutritionists, and beauty consultants are available around the clock. Guests are also offered bespoke cultural experiences including private visits to the Louvre after hours, couture fittings at Chanel's nearby atelier, and helicopter transfers to the Loire Valley châteaux.`,
