    name: "Capella Singapore",
    description: `The discovery of Capella Singapore — approached through 30 acres of mature secondary rainforest on Sentosa Island before the building suddenly reveals itself between the canopy — is one of the great arrival experiences in Asian travel. Norman Foster's design integrates two 19th-century colonial bungalows (the original British Army officers' mess and residences of the 1880s, perfectly preserved) with a striking contemporary intervention of glass, steel, and tropical garden, creating a resort that is simultaneously ancient and modern, formal and intimate, British colonial and vividly contemporary Singaporean.

The 111 villas and suites are distributed across the resort's multiple levels, from the hilltop colonial bungalow accommodations — whose verandas, ceiling fans, and rattan furniture create the most atmospheric bedrooms in Singapore — to the contemporary pool villas at garden level, whose private plunge pools look out through screens of tropical palms toward the Strait of Singapore. The Grand Plantation Estate villa — a restored 1880s colonial house — is perhaps the most historically resonant hotel accommodation in all of Singapore: a complete colonial mansion with five bedrooms, a private garden, a pool, a dedicated butler team, and a programme of personalised experiences developed over the course of the booking process.

Bob's Bar — named for the resort's unofficial resident mascot, a reticulate python who took up residence in the beachfront palms during construction and has never left — is an extraordinary outdoor bar and grill on the beachfront with views of the Strait of Singapore and the tanker traffic of one of the world's busiest shipping channels. The Capella Spa is a comprehensive wellness destination, and the hotel's two swimming pools — including a remarkable adults-only pool overlooking the Strait — are among the finest pool environments in the city.

The resort's cultural programming is the most sophisticated in Singapore, with a dedicated Heritage Concierge who can arrange private museum access, Peranakan home cooking classes with a Babanyonya family in the Katong neighbourhood, Teochew opera performances, and private visits to the city's surviving clan houses and Chinese temple complexes.`,
